---
import ApiCopyButton from "../components/ApiCopyButton.astro";
import ApiPanel from "../components/ApiPanel.astro";
import {
  API_SUCCESSFUL_PATH,
  CURL_DISPLAY,
  SMOKE_TO_TERMINAL_DISPLAY,
} from "../model.ts";

const pathMarkdown = API_SUCCESSFUL_PATH.map(
  (step, index) => `${index + 1}. ${step.label} (${step.href}): ${step.detail}`,
).join("\n");

const markdown = `# API Reference

Local \`/v1\` for evidence-backed media understanding. Live translate guesses; this studies the media first, then returns receipts your pipeline can verify.

Studio and agentic editors are both clients of the same local runtime host. This is not a hosted SaaS API.

## Successful path

Host authority order (not every nav page is a first call):

${pathMarkdown}

Improve (\`/api/improve/\`) is a Concepts page about the miss-to-gold conveyor. It is not a \`/v1\` surface.

An empty list envelope is an honest answer, not an error.

Smoke through caption-seam, opt-in language 201, and same-grant playback panels are one continuous local capture family. Owned ingest, YouTube, review revocation, and default-host caption 409 remain separate families. A shared runtimeId alone is not proof of one journal. Opt-in caption and language 201 panels are not default \`npm run runtime:host\` behavior.

## First verified call

With a running host and bearer token, \`GET /v1/source-sessions\` proves authorization and shows registered sources.

\`\`\`bash
${CURL_DISPLAY}
\`\`\`

## Smoke to terminal

Copy-paste sequence that proves local value without claiming captions or SaaS:

\`\`\`bash
${SMOKE_TO_TERMINAL_DISPLAY}
\`\`\`
`;
---

<header class="api-hero">
  <div class="api-page-header-row">
    <h1>API Reference</h1>
    <ApiCopyButton kind="page" label="Copy page" ariaLabel="Copy page as Markdown" />
  </div>
  <p class="api-lede">
    Local <code>/v1</code> for evidence-backed media understanding. Live translate guesses; this
    studies the media first, then returns receipts your pipeline can verify. Studio and agentic
    editors are both clients of the same local runtime host.
  </p>
  <script is:inline type="application/json" data-api-copy-source set:html={JSON.stringify(markdown)} />
</header>

<section class="api-section" aria-labelledby="api-path-heading">
  <h2 id="api-path-heading">Successful Path</h2>
  <ol class="api-steps">
    {API_SUCCESSFUL_PATH.map((step) => (
      <li>
        <a href={step.href}>{step.label}</a>
        <span class="api-step-detail">{`: ${step.detail}`}</span>
      </li>
    ))}
  </ol>
  <p>
    <a href="/api/improve/">Improve</a> is a Concepts page about the miss-to-gold conveyor. It is
    not a <code>/v1</code> surface. An empty list envelope is an honest answer, not an error.
    Fail-closed reads stay unavailable or withheld instead of inventing output.
  </p>
  <p>
    Smoke through caption-seam, opt-in language 201, and same-grant playback panels are one
    continuous local capture family. Owned ingest, YouTube, review revocation, and default-host
    caption 409 remain separate families. A shared <code>runtimeId</code> alone is not proof of
    one journal. Opt-in caption and language 201 panels are not default
    <code>npm run runtime:host</code> behavior.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="api-section" aria-labelledby="api-first-call-heading">
  <h2 id="api-first-call-heading">First Verified Call</h2>
  <div class="api-split">
    <div>
      <p>
        With a running host and bearer token, <code>GET /v1/source-sessions</code> proves
        authorization and shows what is already registered. Then move to Runtime Lifecycle for the
        study itself.
      </p>
      <p>
        Host on loopback; bearer required. See
        <a href="/api/authentication/">Authentication</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="api-panels">
      <ApiPanel title="First Call" body={CURL_DISPLAY} />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="api-section" aria-labelledby="api-smoke-heading">
  <h2 id="api-smoke-heading">Smoke To Terminal</h2>
  <div class="api-split">
    <div>
      <p>
        Smallest sequence that proves value on the default <code>npm run runtime:host</code>: list
        sources, plan, start, poll the journal to terminal. No model spend. No hosted upload path.
      </p>
      <p>
        Captions come later, only after
        <a href="/api/review/">Publish Review</a>. The default recorded caption executor may refuse
        fixture authority; that is fail-closed, not a missing route. Captured caption 201 panels use
        an opt-in deterministic test seam; Captured language 201 panels need further OpenAI host
        flags. Neither is default host behavior.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="api-panels">
      <ApiPanel title="Smoke · Local Host" body={SMOKE_TO_TERMINAL_DISPLAY} />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
